	"nodes":[
		{"id":"b8a071c8763584a8","type":"text","text":"# Explain the AI pipeline in natural language\n\nFor your **Tech stack — AI pipeline** slide: how voice and documents become answers — without the AI inventing ledger numbers.\n\n---\n\n## 30-second version\n\n> My app has **two AI pipelines**.\n>\n> **Documents:** upload a PDF → extract text → split into chunks → turn into vectors → store in Postgres. When you ask a question, we find the closest chunks and the LLM answers **only from that text** — grounded RAG.\n>\n> **Voice:** you speak into the mic → audio goes to **Whisper** → we get text → same **scenario chat** as typing. Forecast math still runs in code; AI explains and retrieves — it doesn’t make up balances.\n\n---\n\n## Part 1 — Documents (RAG + pgvector + LLM)\n\nWalk the slide **left to right**:\n\n**Upload PDF/image**  \n> “User uploads a bill, insurance policy, or lease on `/documents`.”\n\n**Extract text**  \n> “The server pulls text out — OCR if it’s a scan — so we have searchable content, not just a file sitting in storage.”\n\n**Chunk (1000 chars, 200 overlap)**  \n> “Long documents are **split into pieces** with a little overlap so a sentence isn’t cut in half at the edge. That makes search more accurate.”\n\n**Embedding (384 dimensions)**  \n> “Each chunk is turned into a **vector** — a list of numbers that captures meaning. Similar text gets similar vectors.”\n\n**Store in Postgres + pgvector**  \n> “Vectors live in the database in **`document_chunks`**, alongside the original text. **pgvector** lets us search by similarity fast.”\n\n**User asks a question**  \n> “On Scenario Chat: ‘What is my policy number?’ or ‘What does my insurance bill say?’”\n\n**Embed question → similarity search → top 5 chunks**  \n> “We embed the **same way**, find the **closest chunks**, and pass those excerpts to the LLM — not the whole internet, not the whole ledger guess.”\n\n**LLM (Claude/Gemini) → answer from sources**  \n> “The model writes a **short answer from those excerpts**. If it’s not in the document, it should say **not found** — not invent a policy number.”\n\n**One line:**  \n> “RAG means **retrieve first, then generate** — so document answers stay tied to what you uploaded.”\n\n---\n\n## Part 2 — Voice (OpenAI Whisper)\n\n**Mic → audio**  \n> “On the forecast page, the user taps the microphone.”\n\n**/api/stt/transcribe → OpenAI Whisper**  \n> “Audio goes to my **API route** on the server — the API key stays on Vercel — and **Whisper** converts speech to text.”\n\n**Text → scenario chat**  \n> “That text is fed into the **same chat pipeline** as typing: deterministic ledger, LangGraph, RAG, or forecast advisor — with the **route badge** showing which path ran.”\n\n**One line:**  \n> “Voice is just **input method**; the brain behind the answer is still hybrid routing + Postgres.”\n\n---\n\n## How this fits your “four engines” rule\n\n```text\nDocuments  →  RAG pipeline     →  answers from PDF text\nVoice      →  Whisper → text   →  same orchestrator as chat\nForecast   →  projection.ts    →  NOT the LLM doing math\nChat       →  route badge      →  user sees which engine answered\n```\n\n> “AI **retrieves and explains**. Code **computes** totals and forecasts. That’s the boundary.”\n\n---\n\n## Simple analogy\n\n> “**RAG** is like open-book exam: the model can only use the pages you brought. **Whisper** is dictation: it turns speech into text, then the same tutor reads your ledger and documents. The tutor doesn’t recalculate your bank balance from memory.”\n\n---\n\n## Tie to Obsidian (if they ask)\n\n> “RAG is for **AI at question time**. **Obsidian** is the human-readable wiki export — browse and graph view. Same uploads, different use: machine search vs human reading.”\n\n---\n\n## If someone asks: “Why 384 dimensions?”\n\n> “Smaller embeddings are enough for this MVP — local MiniLM in dev, OpenAI small model in production — both stored at **384 dims** so dev and prod stay compatible in **pgvector**.”\n\n---\n\n## Full picture (one diagram in words)\n\n```text\nPDF upload ──→ chunks + vectors ──→ pgvector\n                                         ↓\nUser question ──→ embed ──→ top chunks ──→ LLM ──→ Ledger + LLM badge\n\nMic ──→ Whisper ──→ text ──→ scenario-chat orchestrator\n                              ├─ deterministic ledger\n                              ├─ LangGraph\n                              ├─ RAG (above)\n                              └─ forecast advisor\n```\n\n---\n\n## Slide subtitle (optional)\n\n> **AI pipeline:** Documents → RAG (chunk, embed, retrieve) · Voice → Whisper → hybrid chat\n\n---\n\n## 15-second closing line\n\n> “The AI pipeline makes the app feel smart on **documents and voice**, but **trust** still comes from deterministic code and the database — the LLM is the narrator and librarian, not the accountant.”","x":-540,"y":-640,"width":1100,"height":980}
	],
